Suppose $$A,B \subseteq X$$ are subsets such that their interiors cover $$X.$$ Then the inclusion $$i\colon (B,A \cap B) \hookrightarrow (X,A)$$ induces isomorphisms $$i_*\colon H_n(B, A \cap B) \to H_n(X,A)$$ for all $$n.$$

